place.name: TADLEY
place.gazetteerText: TADLEY, a parish in Kingsclere district, Hants; 5 miles NNW of Basingstoke r. station. Post town, Basingstoke. Acres, 2,047. Real property, £1,340. Pop., 900. Houses, 191. The living is a rectory, annexed to Overton. There is an Independent chapel. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
